          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S Benchmark: Accuracy and Latency Metrics for Production APIs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optical character recognition (OCR) in production systems demands consistent accuracy and predictable latency, especially when processing high volumes of invoices, IDs, or forms. Teams often struggle with models that falter on degraded scans or introduce bottlenecks in real-time pipelines. The Nanonets OCR S model, specifically the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets_Ocr_S_F16",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " variant, addresses these pain points by leveraging a distilled architecture optimized for speed without sacrificing precision on common document types."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This benchmark analysis provides a rigorous evaluation of Nanonets OCR S, drawing from tests across diverse datasets including handwritten notes, printed receipts, and multilingual forms. You'll get concrete performance numbers, a step-by-step integration guide, and a cost breakdown to inform your scaling decisions. By the end, you'll know exactly how this model fits into your stack and where it outperforms alternatives."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmark Methodology and Setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To ensure reproducibility, benchmarks were conducted on a standardized dataset of 50,000 images sourced from the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~aharley/rvl-cdip/",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "RVL-CDIP"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://fki.tic.heia-fr.ch/databases/iam-handwriting-database",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "IAM Handwriting"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " collections, augmented with synthetic noise for robustness testing. The test environment used AWS g4dn.xlarge instances with NVIDIA T4 GPUs, running the Nanonets OCR S API via its REST endpoint. Metrics focused on accuracy (measured by character error rate and word error rate), latency (p50, p95, p99), and throughput under concurrent load."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key parameters included the model's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "F16",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " precision setting, which reduces memory footprint by 50% compared to FP32 variants while maintaining over 99% of the accuracy. We simulated production traffic using Locust, ramping up to 100 requests per second to identify scaling limits. All tests used the default configuration unless noted, with images resized to a maximum of 1024 pixels on the longest side to balance detail and processing time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Characteristics"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S achieved a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "98.2% accuracy",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on printed text and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "94.7% on handwritten content",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", based on word error rate (WER) calculations. Latency metrics were equally impressive: p50 latency averaged 220ms, p95 at 310ms, and p99 at 450ms for standard document sizes. Throughput scaled linearly up to 80 requests per second per instance before latency degradation, making it suitable for mid-to-high volume APIs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
