      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Note:",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Latency can spike by 20-30% for images exceeding 2048 pixels on the longest side due to additional resizing overhead. Pre-resize images client-side to avoid this."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integration Steps with Nanonets OCR S API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating Nanonets OCR S requires an API key from the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://app.nanonets.com#/keys",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Nanonets dashboard"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and adherence to its RESTful interface. The process involves sending a base64-encoded image or a public URL to the endpoint, with optional parameters for language hints and output formatting. Below is a step-by-step guide to get started."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ol",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
